{
  "slug": "api-design-is-a-promise",
  "title": "API design is a promise",
  "category": "coding",
  "kicker": "Interfaces",
  "hook": "An API is not just a route. It is a promise about names, errors, timing, compatibility, and what future teams can safely assume.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-21",
  "tags": [
    "api-design",
    "contracts"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Clients remember everything",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Once a field ships, someone builds around it. Once an error shape leaks, someone parses it. The API becomes a contract even if nobody wrote the contract down.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "curl · response shape",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "$ curl /v1/subscriptions/sub_123",
              "c": "pr"
            },
            {
              "t": "{ \"status\": \"paused\", \"resumeAt\": \"2026-07-01\" }",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "# clients now depend on both names",
              "c": "dim"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Design the boring cases too",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Document pagination, idempotency, errors, retries, nullability, and versioning before the first client ships. Happy paths are the easy part.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "errors.json",
          "code": "{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"subscription_already_paused\",\n    \"message\": \"Subscription is already paused.\"\n  }\n}",
          "caption": "Stable error codes are kinder than prose scraping."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Treat compatibility as a feature",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Add contract tests for response shapes and error codes. Breaking clients is a production incident even when your server is green.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "stats",
          "items": [
            {
              "to": 1,
              "label": "canonical error envelope"
            },
            {
              "to": 2,
              "label": "versioning choices: evolve or fork"
            },
            {
              "to": 0,
              "label": "undocumented breaking fields"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "04 · the takeaway",
      "heading": "Good APIs reduce future meetings",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">A clear API lets teams move independently because the boundary says what will stay true.</p>"
        },
        {
